defaultDemand Responsi
defaultve Transport exists in several areas between Woodbridge and Beccles. It has a role to play - perhaps best as supplementing
default&#xa0;
default or feeding into rather than replacing scheduled services
default&#xa0;
default For example, at busy times a timetabled bus should run; off-peak DRT may b
defaulte the best solution.
default&#xa0;
default We believe that the Department for Transport should commission a study into the experience so far of DRT - has it fully answered the needs of those iusolated communities which it serves; what proportion of demands from would-be travel
defaultlers have actually been fulfilled; has it contributed to modal shift away from the motor car?
default&#xa0;
defaultFor some journeys there is little alternative to the car - and that applies sometimes for access from isolated rural communities to the nearest rail station. Al
defaultmost all stations on the Ipswich - Lowestoft line have well-used car parks. Such facilities must be encouraged.
default&#xa0;
defaultAll stations between Ipswich and Lowestoft have been unstaffed for many years. It is important that uses are found for redundant station build
defaultings, and both central and local government can use their influence to ensure that this happens.
